sentences: Khia Shamone Finch ( KY-ə; née Chambers; born November 8, 1977) is an American rapper, songwriter, singer, media personality, and record producer.
In 1991, Khia had her first child, a daughter also named Khia.
In 1992, she moved to Hawaii when the father was stationed there and had her second child, a son named Rashawn, while she was living with him.
Her mother Carol Belinda Chambers, who was a data entry specialist, died in 2001.
Khia released her debut album, Thug Misses in 2002 on Dirty Down/Artemis Records as a re-release from the original version by Divine Records.
In 2004, Khia appeared on a track with Trick Daddy and Tampa Tony called "Jump On It" from Trick's album Thug Matrimony: Married to the Streets.
Khia's second album was supposed to be released in 2003 by the title "Street Preacher".
In 2006 Khia recorded another album to be her second album, Gangstress.
Khia's second album, Gangstress, was released on July 11, 2006 on Phase One Communications.
Later in 2006, Khia also collaborated with Janet Jackson on her hit "So Excited", which peaked at #90 on the Hot 100 and #1 on the Hot Dance Club Play chart.

sentences: After signing to Big Cat Records, and still with her own label Thug Misses Entertainment, Khia finished working on her third studio album, Nasti Muzik, released on July 22, 2008.

sentences: Khia began working on her fourth album, MotorMouf aka Khia Shamone, in 2009.
On May 4, 2010, she released the lead single from the album, "Been a Bad Girl".
In 2010, she told the website HipHopDX that the album will feature her singing instead of rapping on some of its cuts.
MotorMouf aka Khia Shamone was released on July 17, 2012.
